{"verses": ["\r\n              Preserve me, O God: for in thee do I put my  trust.", "O my soul, thou hast said unto the Lord, Thou art my Lord:  my goodness extendeth not to thee;", "But to the saints that are in the earth, and to the excellent, in whom is all my delight.", "Their sorrows shall be multiplied that hasten after another  god: their drink offerings of blood will I not offer, nor take up their names into my lips.", "The Lordis the  portion of mine  inheritance and of my cup: thou  maintainest my lot.", "The lines are fallen unto me in pleasant places; yea, I have a goodly heritage.", "I will bless the Lord, who hath given me counsel: my reins also instruct me in the night seasons.", "I have set the  Lord always before me: because he is at my  right hand, I shall not be moved.", "Therefore my heart is glad, and my glory rejoiceth: my  flesh also shall rest in hope.", "For thou wilt not  leave my  soul in  hell; neither wilt thou suffer thine  Holy One to see corruption.", "Thou wilt shew me the path of life: in thy  presenceis fulness of  joy; at thy right hand there are pleasures for evermore."], "book_name": "Psalms", "summary": "A Messianic Psalm of David\u2014He rejoices in the saints that are in the earth; in his own future redemption from hell; in the fact that God will not suffer his Holy One (Christ) to see corruption; and that fulness of joy is found in the Lord\u2019s presence."}